This paper is about improving the performance of neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of GPU for faster computation, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sequence generation models, which are commonly used in tasks such as speech recognition and image captioning, indicating that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
